uiComponent.title: Interactive Element

description.purpose: Novelty counters inform users about the arrival or creation of new items of the kind indicated by the accompanying glyph.
description.composition: The Novelty Counter is an obtrusive counter.
description.effect: They count down  / disappear as soon as the change has been consulted by the user.

rules: There MUST be a way for the user to consult the changes indicated by the Counter. After the consultation, the Novelty Counter SHOULD disappear or the number it contains is reduced by one. Depending on the content, the reduced number might be added in an additional Status Counter.
The Novelty Counter MUST be displayed on the top at the end of the line in reading direction of the item it accompanies. This would be top right for latin script and top left for arabic script.
The Novelty Counter SHOULD have an obtrusive background color such as red or orange.
MAY be used together with the Status Counter.

description.purpose: Buttons are used to trigger interactions that change the systems status. Usually Buttons are contained inside an Input Collection. The Toolbar is the one main exception to this rule, since buttons in the Toolbar might also perform view changes.
description.composition: A Button is a clickable, graphically obtrusive control element. It can bear Text, a Glyph or both as caption.
description.effect: On click, the action indicated by the button is carried out.

rivals.name: Glyphs
rivals.description: Are used if the enclosing Container Collection can not provide enough space for textual information or if such an information would clutter the screen.

rivals.name: Links
rivals.description: Links are used to trigger Interactions that do not change the systems status. They are usually contained inside a Navigational Collection.

rules.description: The caption of Buttons SHOULD contain no more than two words.
A Counter MUST only be used in combination with a glyph.
A Counter MUST contain exactly one number greater than zero and no other characters.
